Peanut Butter Bread
  --B. Dylan Hollis

2 c flour
pinch salt
1/4 c sugar
4 tsp baking powder
1 1/3 c milk
1/2 c peanut butter

Preheat oven to 325F. Combine flour, salt, sugar, and baking powder in a bowl. Add milk and peanut butter, fold until combined. Pour into loaf pan and bake for ~1 hr & 10 min. Cool before slicing.



Alt @wickdconfections

1 3/4 c (220 g) ap flour
1/2 c (100 g) sugar
1/4 c (50 g) brown sugar
1 tbsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1 c (240 ml) milk
3/4 c (190 g) creamy peanut butter
1 tsp vanilla extract
Optional topping: 2 tbsp sugar

Preheat oven to 350F / 175C. Grease a 9×5" loaf pan. Whisk flour, sugars, baking powder, salt. Add milk, peanut butter, vanilla. Mix until just combined. Spread into pan, sprinkle sugar if using. Bake 50–60 min until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 15 min, remove, slice.

Molasses Glaze
2 tbsp (28 g) butter
3 tbsps (45 ml) molasse
2 tbsp (30 ml) milk
1 c (120 g) powdered sugar
1/4 tsp vanilla + pinch salt
Optional: pinch cinnamon or ginger

Melt butter, whisk in molasses + milk until warm. Remove from heat and whisk in powdered sugar until smooth. Stir in vanilla and salt.


Melt butter, whisk in molasses + milk until warm. Remove from heat and whisk in powdered sugar until smooth. Stir in vanilla and salt.
